    Example problem data

    prize_wheel.Rd

    Data from chapter 11 of MA206's text book

    Usage

    prize_wheel

    Format

    prize_wheel

    A data frame with 3 rows and 3 columns:

    sector_type

    type of pie slice from prize wheel

    frequency

    proportion of pie slice of that type

    payout

    how much is paid out in the case landing on slice

    ...

    Source

    Examples

    prize_wheel
#>   sector_type frequency payout
#> 1    No Prize         9      0
#> 2      Win $1         1      1
#> 3      Win $3         2      3

library(ggplot2)
ggplot(prize_wheel) +
    aes(x = payout, y = frequency) +
    geom_lollipop()


prize_wheel %>%
  merge(prize_wheel, by = NULL) %>%
  merge(prize_wheel, by = NULL) %>%
  merge(prize_wheel, by = NULL)
